@page
@model IndexModel
@{
    ViewData["Title"] = "Evolution of Cloud Computing";
}

<style>
    body {
        font-family: 'Arial', sans-serif;
        background-color: #8ED2FFFF;
        margin: 0;
        padding: 0;
    }

    h2 {
        color: #2c3e50;
        font-size: 2.5rem;
        text-align: center;
        margin-top: 40px;
        text-transform: uppercase;
        letter-spacing: 1px;
    }

    .content-wrapper {
        max-width: 900px;
        margin: 0 auto;
        padding: 20px;
        background-color: #B9B9B9FF;
        box-shadow: 0 8px 16px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.1);
        border-radius: 10px;
        margin-top: 30px;
    }

    .image-container {
        text-align: center;
        margin-bottom: 40px;
    }

    .image-container img {
        max-width: 100%;
        height: auto;
        border-radius: 10px;
       
    }

    p {
        font-size: 1.2rem;
        line-height: 1.6;
        color: #34495e;
        text-align: justify;
        margin-top: 20px;
    }

    ul {
        list-style: none;
        padding: 0;
        margin: 20px 0;
    }

    li {
        font-size: 1.2rem;
        background-color: #ecf0f1;
        padding: 15px;
        border-radius: 8px;
        margin-bottom: 15px;
        display: flex;
        align-items: center;
        transition: background-color 0.3s ease;
    }

    li:hover {
        background-color: #d0d8db;
    }

    li strong {
        margin-right: 10px;
        color: #2980b9;
        font-size: 1.3rem;
    }

 
</style>

<div class="content-wrapper">
    <div class="image-container">
        <img src="https://tse3.mm.bing.net/th?id=OIP.OhusEDQXDMzbKqTRwaAg1AHaDs&pid=Api&P=0&h=220" alt="Cloud Computing Evolution">
    </div>

    <h2>Evolution of Cloud Computing</h2>

    <p>
        Cloud computing has rapidly transformed from basic networking concepts to the sophisticated cloud infrastructure we know today. Its evolution can be broken down into key phases:
    </p>

    <ul>
        <li><strong>1960s:</strong> The idea of computing as a service was introduced. Early concepts of networking, such as ARPANET (precursor to the internet), laid the foundation.</li>
        <li><strong>1990s:</strong> Virtualization revolutionized computing by allowing multiple operating systems to run on a single physical machine. This made data centers more efficient and scalable.</li>
        <li><strong>Early 2000s:</strong> Companies like Amazon (AWS) and Microsoft (Azure)launched large-scale cloud platforms, offering storage, computing power, and other services over the internet, marking the beginning of modern cloud computing.</li>
        <li><strong>2010s:</strong> The explosion of cloud platforms enabled multi-cloud and hybrid cloud environments, improving flexibility, cost-efficiency, and reliability.</li>
        <li><strong>2020s and beyond:</strong> Cloud computing continues to evolve with innovations in edge computing, serverless architecture, and AI-powered cloud services, allowing for more powerful and seamless integrations across industries.</li>
    </ul>

    
</div>
